commit.message:
Always execute the latest brightness change request instead of queuing (#95)

Remove brightness request queue

At each moment, only the most recent request should be executed. Else
rapidly changing the brightness up and down in System Preferences resulted in a series of brightness changes which continued long after the end of setting change.

Support all valid Core Display Clock frequencies to fix the kernel panic on Intel ICL platforms (#62)

* Implement the maximum link rate fix for some laptops with 4K display.

* Added the manual for the DPCD max link rate fix.

* Fix the formatting issue in the manual.

* Adjust the alignment of the screen capture in the manual.

* Adjust the code style.

* A better approach to retrieve the current framebuffer index.

* [SYNC] Replace the DPCD image in the manual.

* Fix the indentation in kern_igfx.

* Add the driver support for onboard LSPCON chips to enable DisplayPort to HDMI 2.0 output.

* Update the change log and fix a typo.

* Update the README.

* Added the manual for LSPCON driver support.

* Improve the return type of AppleIntelFramebufferController::ReadAUX().

* Fix the infinite loop when calculating dividers for HDMI connection on SKL, KBL and CFL platforms.

* Update the README and change log for the infinite loop fix.

* Update the manual for the infinite loop fix and improve the comments.

* Improve the formatting in the manual

* Attempt to fix the memory analyzer warning.

* Improve the verbose output when -igfxi2cverbose is specified.

* Fix the unused variable warning under RELEASE configurations.

* Improve the error message in ComputeHdmiP0P1P2.

* Improve the code style; several minor fixes.

* Improve the deleter by adding the NONNULL attribute; Implement the getIndex helper.

* User should use DEBUG version to enable verbose I2C-over-AUX output.

* Remove the property `LSPCON::isActive` and always read the latest mode from the adapter as some LSPCON adapters are automatically switched back to LS mode on power off (i.e. Cable removal, sleep/wake up cycle).

* Update the change log.

* Fix the maximum link rate value in the extended DPCD buffer as well. (e.g. Dell Inspiration 7590 with Sharp display)

* Update the manual for the new max link rate fix.

* Update the changelog.

* Merge from upstream: Resolve conflicts.

* CDC: Add support for valid yet unsupported Core Display Clock (CDCLK) frequencies on ICL platforms to avoid the kernel panic.

* CDC: Fix an issue that the reference frequency is not properly decoded.

* CDC: Fix a typo in the switch statement.

* CDC: Update the README.

* CDC: Update the change log.

* CDC: Update the manual.

* CDC: Fix a typo.

* CDC: Always print the clock frequency before and after sanitized.

* CDC: Fix the analyzer warning.

* CDC: Leftover: No need to erase the prefix for functions that are no longer routed for debugging.

* CDC: Use the shared ReadRegister32() function.

commit.message:
Port i915 force wake workaround (#49)

Port of i915 force wake. The difference with Apple code is as follows:

 connectivity.

 to DP.
 This breaks many systems, so we undo this check.
 Affected drivers: KBL and newer?

commit.message:
Add option to force enable Metal for offline iGPU (#45)

By default, `IntelAccelerator::start` will remove the property `MetalPluginName` if the number of
framebuffers is 0. On Macs and Hackintoshes alike, this means that an iGPU with no connectors cannot
be used for Metal's compute APIs.

This new option will re-add `MetalPluginName` in order to allow Metal to be used.
